    <string name="diag_info_title">How symbol scanning works</string>
    <string name="diag_info_body_1">DexKit opens the installed Google App APK and uses structural fingerprints (field types, extension numbers, inheritance) to locate the obfuscated classes, fields, and methods this module hooks. Results are cached by longVersionCode.</string>
    <string name="diag_info_body_2">When Google App updates, rescan to rebuild the cache. A missing symbol means the obfuscation shifted and the fingerprint needs updating.</string>

